text: The atmosphere is very aesthetic and the food is tasty. Really taste like homemade food. The handmade noodle was very nice.

I recently discovered this charming, trendy spot that offers delicious, homemade yong tau foo. They also feature daily specials, like the dry mee siam I had today, which was incredibly flavorful. The restaurant is family-owned, and the owners are warm and welcoming. It's a newly opened place that truly deserves support. If you're in the area, definitely give it a try!
Clean and nice environment. The food is good too. The lady boss is very friendly and chatty.
